    {
      "text": "Tail Concerto is an action-adventure platform video game developed by CyberConnect and published by Bandai for the PlayStation. It is the first game to be developed by CyberConnect, as well as the first installment in the Little Tail Bronx series, which takes place in a steampunk fantasy world of floating islands populated by anthropomorphic dogs and cats. The game revolves around a teenaged canine police officer named Waffle Ryebread and his encounters with the Black Cats Gang, a group of sky pirates who aim to steal magic crystals. Though it received a generally positive response from critics, the title was met with low sales in Japan, falling short of the publisher's expectations.\nTail Concerto was first released in Japan in April 1998 and the following December in France, with an English version released in North America in November 1999 by publisher Atlus USA. The game features character designs and artwork by manga artist Nobuteru Yūki, and the Japanese version included the opening theme song \"For Little Tail\" performed by Kokia before her debut in the music business.",
      "lang": "en",
      "source": "wikipedia_en"
    }
